An open source ticketing system is a great solution for managing customer inquiries, support requests, or any other communication with customers. Hence, it is used to match tickets with customer requests and issues. Every ticket generated is tracked and stored in the system. It allows proxies to coalesce multiple requests. An open source ticketing system is a solution that any business can use. Everyone can use it, including your business. The company benefits in many ways. First, it allows customers to report problems online. No need to bombard you with calls and emails. You may be wondering, "What about my support team?" Well, an open source ticketing system can allow your support team to resolve customer issues faster. Ultimately, this will keep your existing customers happy.
